- event
    - high-level umbrella term for user-input events or derived events as a consequence of user events
    - has a duration
- segment
    - events may be divided into multiple segments
    - by default, an event is at least one segment (in which case they're practically equivalent)
    - most segments are affected by time-stops
    - cooldown segments are not affected by time-stops
- frame
    - a discrete point in time (120 frames in a second)
    - point in time when important game mechanics occur, such as:
        - status effects are applied
        - skills cause damage
    - segments may contain multiple frames 
- status
    - event applying buff or debuff
